 NGOZI OKORIE THE Delta State Police Command has recovered the decomposing corpses of two children in an abandoned car at Abraka, Ethiope East Local Government Area of the state. Acting Police Public Relations Officer in Delta, Bright Edafe, said the corpses were sighted in a Honda Rover car with registration number AG 815 BKW, parked in the path way of the house of a man, simply identified as Mr. Tayo. Edafe, who disclosed this in a statement, said the vehicle belonged to the said Mr. Tayo, aged 35 years. He noted that the Divisional Police Officer, CSP Aliyu Shaba, led police operatives to the scene immediately and evacuated the corpses. The police identified the corpses as Kelvin izakpa ‘m’ aged 10 years and Fega Izakpa ‘m’ aged 7 years, both children of late Meshach Izakpa. “They were staying with their mother before their disappearance,” the statement said. The PPRO however said investigation was still ongoing, noting that the decomposing corpses had been handed to the family for burial while the suspect had been arrested and his vehicle impounded. 